      "writtenOn": "2018-09-04T19:06:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Nothing. :) For all the RGB(A) formats, there are two versions: RGB and BGR. Mike arranged the enum so that the low bit encodes the R/B swap. To keep that logic intact for single-channel formats like Gray, there are two copies of the Gray enum value. So using G_8_ will do the same splat of the single-channel source to RGB, then swap the two identical values.",
      "parentUuid": "fd9ccef5_332bf136",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 613,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 613,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "468e3031634dd7b9cc9634149fbcc099fbcd4db2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
